<section class="bg-ink-800 text-cream">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="max-w-3xl py-16 md:py-20">
      <p class="eyebrow eyebrow--on-dark">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mt-5 text-display-sm text-cream">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-paper-200/70">Last updated: <%= updated %></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-y">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-prose">
<% if (!isProd) { %>
      <%# Owner-facing reminder — only renders in non-production builds. %>
      <div class="mb-10 rounded-2xl border border-clay-400/30 bg-clay-400/[0.08] p-5">
        <p class="text-sm text-paper-200/80">
          <strong class="font-semibold text-cream">Dev note (hidden in production):</strong> This is a
          clean starter policy. Have it reviewed by a qualified legal professional and tailored to your
          jurisdiction and actual data practices before launch.
        </p>
      </div>
<% } %>

      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none prose-headings:font-display prose-headings:text-cream prose-h2:text-2xl prose-h2:mt-12 prose-h3:text-lg prose-a:text-clay-400 prose-a:no-underline hover:prose-a:underline prose-strong:text-cream text-paper-200/75">
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy explains how <%= site.brand.legalName %> (“Veylrio”, “we”, “us”) collects,
          uses and protects information when you visit <%= site.brand.domain %> or contact us through
          this website.
        </p>

        <h2>Information we collect</h2>
        <p>We collect only what we need to respond to you and operate this site:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Information you provide.</strong> When you submit the “Start a Project” form, we collect the details you enter — such as your name, company, email, phone or WhatsApp number, industry, your current outbound situation, current dialer/CRM, what you want to build or fix, preferred contact method, timeline and optional budget range.</li>
          <li><strong>Technical information.</strong> Standard server logs may record information such as your IP address, browser type and the pages you request, used to keep the site secure and reliable.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How we use your information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To review your inquiry and respond through your preferred contact method.</li>
          <li>To understand your operation so we can suggest a practical next step.</li>
          <li>To operate, secure and improve this website.</li>
          <li>To comply with legal obligations where they apply.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Legal basis for processing</h2>
        <p>
          Where applicable law (such as the GDPR) requires a legal basis, we rely on your consent and
          on our legitimate interest in responding to inquiries and running our business. You can
          withdraw consent or object at any time by contacting us.
        </p>

        <h2>How we share information</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell your personal information. We may share it with trusted service providers who
          help us operate the site and communicate with you (for example, email or hosting providers),
          and only as needed to provide those services. We may also disclose information where required
          by law.
        </p>

        <h2>Data retention</h2>
        <p>
          We keep inquiry details for as long as needed to respond and to maintain a reasonable record
          of our communications, after which we delete or anonymise them, unless a longer period is
          required by law.
        </p>

        <h2>Security</h2>
        <p>
          We apply reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect your information,
          including secure transport (HTTPS), restricted access and input validation. No method of
          transmission or storage is completely secure, however, and we cannot guarantee absolute
          security.
        </p>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete or restrict the
          use of your personal information, or to object to processing and request portability. To
          exercise any of these, email us at
          <a href="mailto:<%= site.contactEmail %>"><%= site.contactEmail %></a>.
        </p>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          This site uses a single, strictly necessary cookie to protect forms against cross-site
          request forgery. It is not used for advertising or cross-site tracking. We do not load
          third-party advertising or analytics cookies by default; if that changes, this policy will be
          updated.
        </p>

        <h2>Third-party links</h2>
        <p>
          Our site may link to third-party websites. We are not responsible for their content or
          privacy practices, and we encourage you to review their policies.
        </p>

        <h2>Children</h2>
        <p>
          This site is intended for businesses and is not directed to children. We do not knowingly
          collect personal information from children.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy from time to time. We will revise the “Last updated” date above
          when we do.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy or your information? Email
          <a href="mailto:<%= site.contactEmail %>"><%= site.contactEmail %></a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
